‚≠ê Steps to Install a Basic Web Server (Apache) on a Cloud VM
1. Connect to the Cloud Virtual Machine

Use SSH to connect to the Linux VM from the local system:

ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@<public-ip>


This opens the terminal of the cloud server.

2. Update System Packages

Run the update command to refresh the package list:

sudo apt update


This ensures that the latest versions of packages are installed.

3. Install the Apache Web Server

Install Apache using the package manager:

sudo apt install apache2 -y


Apache will start automatically after installation.

4. Create a Simple HTML Webpage

Navigate to the default web directory:

cd /var/www/html


Create or edit the homepage file:

sudo nano index.html


Add a basic HTML message such as:

<h1>Welcome to the Cloud VM Web Server</h1>


Save and exit the editor.

5. Allow HTTP Traffic (Port 80)

Ensure that port 80 is open in the cloud platform's firewall or security group settings so the webpage can be viewed publicly.

6. Access the Webpage Using Public IP

Open any web browser and enter:

http://<public-ip>


The custom HTML webpage will appear if Apache is running correctly.
